<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10771471-ayla"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1544598609i/10771471._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10771471-ayla">Ayla</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I asked myself that, at first, because obviously with Jacob, if he didn't have foreknowledge or whatever you decide to believe, then he wouldnt even h<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I asked myself that, at first, because obviously with Jacob, if he didn't have foreknowledge or whatever you decide to believe, then he wouldnt even have recognized his parents as elderly, would he have? But they do seem to realize they're dead, and process that, accordingly, to the age they were when they died and the intellect and reasoning processes they had then. And also, he may have been shown pictures? Because, you know, this was still in the beginning, when he was part of a miracle. I mean, if he rated a flight from china and a personal escort back home, it seems logical that Bellamy could have briefed him, in a way?? And i think they must have dug up the graves, and the bodies were gone, because it says at the end that when they had died that they bodies were returned, right?<br /><a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
