<div id="review_1711004045" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1711004045" />
    <a title="Bandit" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4528663-bandit"><img alt="Bandit" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1289488158p2/4528663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1711004045?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bandit" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bandit" href="/user/show/4528663-bandit">Bandit</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20982851-the-returned">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1711004045" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer159758084090706452">Some years ago I watched and sort of liked a tv show based on this book. Not so much that I continue watching it and at any rate it only lasted two seasons, but I did want to see what happened and so I thought I&apos;d check out the book. Funny thing is that you don&apos;t actually find out, not in the way I was after. Mott took an extraordinary event of the dead randomly coming back to life (and being treated with acceptance, kindness and understanding the world in general and small towns in particular a</span>
  <span id="freeText159758084090706452" style="display:none">Some years ago I watched and sort of liked a tv show based on this book. Not so much that I continue watching it and at any rate it only lasted two seasons, but I did want to see what happened and so I thought I'd check out the book. Funny thing is that you don't actually find out, not in the way I was after. Mott took an extraordinary event of the dead randomly coming back to life (and being treated with acceptance, kindness and understanding the world in general and small towns in particular are so known for treating something different or something they don't understand...yes, that's sarcasm) and used it to frame a small story set in a small town...and I just thought there'd be more to it. Apparently Mott didn't, he deliberately chose to concentrate on personal dynamics over the grand scheme of things and he did it quite well, but this is just a case of unmet expectations. Adding to the fact that the beauty of small southern towns remains a mystery to me. I think a lot more might have been done with the story. It's nicely written, Mott is also a poet and it shows in the subtle beauty of language, it reads easily and fairly quickly, but it was just sort of kind of like building a spaceship and traveling to Missouri in it. The originality of the premise wasted or at the very least left dramatically underused. Should have been more exciting of a read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="159758084090706452" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


